meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct,0.1,217,Q2,original,Who developed the theory of relativity?,"The theory of relativity was developed by Albert Einstein, a renowned German-born physicist. Einstein's theory of relativity is a fundamental concept in modern physics that revolutionized our understanding of space, time, and gravity.

There are two main components to Einstein's theory of relativity:

1. **Special Relativity (1905)**: This theory posits that the laws of physics are the same for all observers in uniform motion relative to one another. It challenged the long-held notion of absolute time and space, and introduced the concept of time dilation and length contraction.
