**History**: Tokyo has a rich history dating back to the 15th century, when it was a small fishing village called Edo. Over time, it grew into a major city and became the capital of Japan in 1868, following the Meiji Restoration. The city was renamed Tokyo, which means ""Eastern Capital"" in Japanese.

