meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct,0.5,292,Q1,original,What causes seasons on Earth?,"The primary cause of seasons on Earth is the tilt of its axis (about 23.5 degrees) in relation to its orbital plane around the Sun. This tilt results in the variation of the amount of solar energy the Earth receives throughout the year, leading to the changing seasons.

