meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct,0.5,294,Q3,original,Why is the sky blue?,"The sky appears blue because of a phenomenon called scattering, which occurs when sunlight interacts with the tiny molecules of gases in the Earth's atmosphere, such as nitrogen (N2) and oxygen (O2).

