The theory of relativity is most closely associated with **Albert Einstein**. 

He developed both **special relativity** (published in 1905) and **general relativity** (published in 1915). 

While Einstein is the most famous name, it's important to note that the development of these theories was a collaborative effort involving many other physicists and mathematicians. 

