meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct,0.1,376,Q6,expert,You are an expert. Answer the following question: How does photosynthesis work?,"Photosynthesis is the fascinating process by which plants, algae, and some bacteria convert light energy from the sun into chemical energy in the form of organic compounds, such as glucose. This complex process is essential for life on Earth, as it provides the energy and organic compounds needed to support the food chain.

