2. **General Relativity (1915)**: Einstein expanded his earlier work and developed the theory of general relativity, which describes gravity as the curvature of spacetime caused by massive objects. According to general relativity, the curvature of spacetime around a massive object such as the Earth causes objects to fall towards the center of the Earth, which we experience as gravity.

