meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct,1.5,439,Q5,noisy,Is artificial intelligence dangerous?,"The question of whether artificial intelligence (AI) is dangerous is complex and has been debated extensively among experts in the field, ethicists, and the broader public. The potential dangers of AI can be broadly categorized into several areas, though it's important to note that the consensus is not that AI itself is inherently dangerous, but rather how it is designed, used, and controlled can pose risks. Here are some potential dangers and concerns:

