meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct,2.0,348,Q3,step_by_step,Explain step by step: Why is the sky blue?,"The sky appears blue because of a phenomenon called Rayleigh scattering, which is named after the British physicist Lord Rayleigh. Here's a step-by-step explanation of why the sky appears blue:

